verses.text: And it came to pass, when men began to multiply on the face of the earth , and daughters were born unto them,
That the sons of God saw the daughters of men that they \add were\add* fair ; and they took them wives of all which they chose.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said , My spirit shall not always strive with man , for that he also \add is\add* flesh : yet his days shall be an hundred and twenty years. \p

There were giants in the earth in those days ; and also after that , when the sons of God came in unto the daughters of men , and they bare \add children\add* to them, the same \add became\add* mighty men which \add were\add* of old , men of renown. \p

¶ And \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* saw that the wickedness of man \add was\add* great in the earth , and \add that\add* every imagination of the thoughts of his heart \add was\add* only evil continually.\f + \fr 6.5 \ft every…: or, the whole imagination: the Hebrew word signifieth not only the imagination, but also the purposes and desires\f*\f + \fr 6.5 \ft continually: Heb. every day\f* \p
And it repented the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* that he had made man on the earth , and it grieved him at his heart.

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said , I will destroy man whom I have created from the face of the earth ; both man , and beast , and the creeping thing , and the fowls of the air ; for it repenteth me that I have made them.\f + \fr 6.7 \ft both…: Heb. from man unto beast\f* \p
But Noah found grace in the eyes of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ These \add are\add* the generations of Noah : Noah was a just man \add and\add* perfect in his generations , \add and\add* Noah walked with God.\f + \fr 6.9 \ft perfect: or, upright\f*
And Noah begat three sons , Shem , Ham , and Japheth. \p
The earth also was corrupt before God , and the earth was filled with violence.
And God looked upon the earth , and, behold, it was corrupt ; for all flesh had corrupted his way upon the earth. \p

And God said unto Noah , The end of all flesh is come before me ; for the earth is filled with violence through them ; and, behold, I will destroy them with the earth.\f + \fr 6.13 \ft with the earth: or, from the earth\f* \p
¶ Make thee an ark of gopher wood ; rooms shalt thou make in the ark , and shalt pitch it within and without with pitch.\f + \fr 6.14 \ft rooms: Heb. nests\f*

And this \add is the fashion\add* which thou shalt make it \add of:\add* The length of the ark \add shall be\add* three hundred cubits , the breadth of it fifty cubits , and the height of it thirty cubits.

A window shalt thou make to the ark , and in a cubit shalt thou finish it above ; and the door of the ark shalt thou set in the side thereof ; \add with\add* lower , second , and third \add stories\add* shalt thou make it.

And, behold , I , even I, do bring a flood of waters upon the earth , to destroy all flesh , wherein \add is\add* the breath of life , from under heaven ; \add and\add* every thing that \add is\add* in the earth shall die.
But with thee will I establish my covenant ; and thou shalt come into the ark , thou , and thy sons , and thy wife , and thy sons’ wives with thee.
And of every living thing of all flesh , two of every \add sort\add* shalt thou bring into the ark , to keep \add them\add* alive with thee; they shall be male and female.
Of fowls after their kind , and of cattle after their kind , of every creeping thing of the earth after his kind , two of every \add sort\add* shall come unto thee, to keep \add them\add* alive.
And take thou unto thee of all food that is eaten , and thou shalt gather \add it\add* to thee; and it shall be for food for thee, and for them.
Thus did Noah ; according to all that God commanded him, so did he.
